[C] Consider the following code snippet that executes the POSIX `stat` call on the file `script.sh`. Check ONLY the options that are MINIMALLY necessary so that the execution displays the text "ABC". (1p)

```c
struct stat info;
if (stat("script.sh", &info) == 0) {
  if (info.st_mode & S_IWUSR) printf("A");
  if (info.st_mode & S_IRGRP) printf("B");
  if (info.st_mode & S_IXOTH) printf("C");
}
```

